│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ I've finally found the critical piece of code.                                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ At line `14585`, `SubVectorsMask` is initialized from `E->ReorderIndices`.                                                                                                               │
│ At line `14593`, `SubVectorsMask.clear()` is called if `SubVectors` is empty or `SubVectorsMask` was already empty.                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ In the case of the reproducer, we are just gathering `icmp` instructions. There are no sub-vectors and no reordering needed. So `SubVectors` is empty, and `E->ReorderIndices` is empty. │
│ This means `SubVectorsMask` is cleared at line `14593`.                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Later, `ShuffleBuilder.finalize` is called with this empty `SubVectorsMask`. However, the `ShuffleBuilder` (`ShuffleCostEstimator`) has been processing scalars and has built up its     │
│ internal `CommonMask` to the size of the vector. This size mismatch causes the crash.                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The fix is to not clear `SubVectorsMask` but to resize it to the vector width, filled with poison elements. This indicates that no sub-vector shuffling is happening.                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will change `SubVectorsMask.clear();` to `SubVectorsMask.assign(GatheredScalars.size(), PoisonMaskElem);`. `GatheredScalars` holds the scalars for the vector, so its size is the      │
│ vector width. `PoisonMaskElem` is `-1`.                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ This change should ensure that `SubVectorsMask` has the correct size when passed to `finalize`.                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/SubVectorsMask.clear();/SubVectorsMask.assign(GatheredScalars.size(), PoisonMaskElem);/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                                       │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
